<section id="section-7">
<title> Summary
</title>

<para id="element-60">
<term>1:</term> Uniform rolling means pure rolling with constant velocity.
</para>
<para id="element-61">
<term>2:</term> Rolling with constant velocity means constant linear velocity of COM and constant angular velocity of rigid body about the axis of rotation.
</para>
<para id="element-62">
<term>3:</term> There is no friction involved in uniform rolling.
</para>
<para id="element-52"><term>4:</term> An accelerated rolling is described by “equation of accelerated rolling” as given by :
</para>
