</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-54"><term>5:</term> The equation of accelerated rolling underlines the fact that there can not be selective acceleration. In other words, if there is linear acceleration, there is corresponding angular acceleration as well.
</para>
<para id="element-55"><term>6:</term> Governing laws of rolling motion are Newton’s second law of motion for translation and rotation. These two laws are subject to the condition imposed by equation of accelerated rolling as given above.
</para>
